    "headline": "GameStop makes bold $56 billion play for eBay, ready to go hostile",
    "summary": "GameStop proposed on Sunday to buy eBay Inc for about $56 billion in a cash-and-stock deal, with CEO Ryan Cohen saying he was prepared to take the bid directly to shareholders should eBay's board be unreceptive.  GameStop - once a stock market minnow that shot to fame ‌during a meme-stock frenzy five years ago - is offering to pay $125 a share in a 50-50 mix of cash and stock, Cohen said in a letter ‌to eBay's board.  Based on eBay's Friday close, the bid represents a premium of about 20%.",
